# Axodus Nucleus Maturity Framework

Last updated: 2026-06-03

## Recast Baseline

RECAST 00 artifacts were not present in `/opt/Axodus/.instructions` during this audit. This framework is recorded in RECAST 01 under the coordinator-approved execution gate from the request text and is now the active baseline for this audit.

This framework is for audit and portfolio planning. It does not grant production authority, execution authority, settlement authority, wallet-signing authority, trading authority, swap authority, payout authority, or treasury authority.

## Maturity Levels

| Level | Name | Meaning |
|---:|---|---|
| L0 | Não Mapeado | No reliable local evidence of purpose, status, or operating boundary. |
| L1 | Documentado | Instructions, status, purpose, or roadmap evidence exists, but validation and runtime evidence are absent or stale. |
| L2 | Validado | Local validation commands are known and have passing or explicitly documented evidence, or a limited validation baseline is documented. |
| L3 | Mock/Local | Mock data, fixtures, local adapters, local services, or non-executing workflows exist with some test or implementation evidence. |
| L4 | Visível no App | The nucleus has visible read-only or mock UI/API surfaces in AxodusAPP or an equivalent local interface. |
| L5 | Contratualizado | Formal contracts, interfaces, API schemas, route contracts, policy matrices, package contracts, or registry contracts exist. |
| L6 | Integrado Local | Local backend/app/API/service integration is proven across nuclei or services without production execution. |
| L7 | Candidato a Produção | A production-readiness gate has explicit governance, security, audit, deployment, rollback, monitoring, and operational evidence. |

## Portfolio States

| State | Meaning |
|---|---|
| ADVANCE | Ready for the next maturity step inside approved local/mock/read-only boundaries. |
| HOLD | Do not advance until portfolio balance improves or an explicit gate is approved. |
| RECOVER | Needs documentation, validation, or hygiene repair before normal progression. |
| AUDIT MORE | Evidence is insufficient for reliable classification. |
| BACKLOG | Valid work exists but is not a current portfolio priority. |

## Confidence

| Confidence | Use |
|---|---|
| High | Multiple local evidence sources agree, with recent status or validation documentation. |
| Medium | Evidence exists but was not freshly validated during this audit. |
| Low | Evidence is incomplete, stale, missing, or mostly inferred from structure. |

## Boundary Rules

- `LOCAL_VALIDATED`, L3, L4, L5, and L6 do not imply production readiness.
- L7 must not be assigned without explicit governance, security, audit, deployment, rollback, monitoring, and operational evidence.
- Financial, execution, trading, DEX, treasury, settlement, marketplace minting, payout, lottery, mining payout, wallet-signing, or on-chain behavior is production-blocked by default.
- A mature subtrack does not automatically raise the full nucleus. Use the lower overall level for portfolio average and document advanced subtracks separately.
- Missing evidence lowers classification.
